cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with learning embeddings for point-clouds, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of self-supervision, which is a common technique in unsupervised learning (cs.AI). The incorporation of local geometric information suggests that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the applications of clustering, semantic analogies, and point-correspondence suggest that it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
